{"id": 5551, "title": "Ticket #5551: Improve classad ingestion performance by presizing hash table", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen we read a classad off the wire, the first thing we read is how many attributes it will have.  The classad implementation stores the set of name-value pairs in a hash table.  By default, this hash table is born small, and is resized as attributes are inserted.  This resizing can be expensive.  By exposing a rehash method, we can tell the classad at birth how many attributes to expect (as least initially).  Tests show this improves the speed of classad ingestions almost 10%.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\nAfter discussion, cherry picked back to 8.5.3</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Mar-23 14:31</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d2836c3b39be6b4d95f12cc5585947eb4334f554\">[48090]</a></span>: Add version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5551\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5551'); return false;\" title=\"Improve classad ingestion performance by presizing hash table\">#5551</a></span>  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Mar-16 11:13</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/e3cfd6a75317fbd700381bebca6943cffaffb5d7\">[48036]</a></span>: Expose classad::rehash to improve ingestion performance <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wi